INT. LIBRARY - DAY

A hand-lettered sign reads *CLOSED FOR RENOVATION*, but the door is open anyway.

NADIA runs a finger along a shelf of _very_ old books.

NADIA
This one's **important**. Don't let it out of your sight.

She hands over a battered volume. The title is barely legible: ***The Cartographer's Warning***.

NADIA (CONT'D)
And whatever you do -- _do not_ open it near water.

A distant clap of thunder. Nadia glances at the window, unimpressed.

NADIA (CONT'D)
Too late for that, I suppose.
